==English==
===Pronunciation===
*noiz, /nɔɪz/, /<tt>nOIz</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪz|Rhymes: -ɔɪz]]

===Noun===
'''noise''' (plural: [[noises]])

#Various sounds, usually unwanted.  (''He knew that it was [[trash]] day, when the [[garbage]] collectors made all the '''noise'''.'')
#Sound or signal generated by random [[fluctuation]]s
#(Tech.) Unwanted part of a [[signal]]. (''Signal to noise ratio'')
#(Genetics) the measured level of variation in gene expression among cells, regardless of source, within a supposedly identical population 

See also: [[sound]], [[bang]], [[boom]], [[crash]], [[thud]].

